    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the climate stuff, but when you say it's \"undeniable\" and that coal is \"unsustainable,\" it sounds like you're saying the debate is already over. isn't it kind of dismissive to just call it a \"trend\" when real people's livelihoods are being phased out by policy? what about the argument that energy security and low costs depend on having reliable baseload power like coal? isn't that a valid point or is that just something people say to stall?",
